flowRoot.flowPara: To run Fedora Workstation, you will need:
Fedora Media Writer (download now)
A USB flash drive with at least $HOW_MUCH space available

Fedora Workstation is provided via Fedora Media Writer. Download this program via the download link above and run it on your system, following the prompts to generate a live version (see "What does 'Live' mean?" in the right sidebar) of Fedora Workstation on a USB flash drive. You may then run the live version of Fedora Workstation from your USB flash drive.

Optionally, you may install Fedora Workstation to a laptop or desktop computer that has at least $CPU processor, $RAM RAM, and $DISK space available. To do this, run the live version of Fedora Workstation from your USB flash drive on the computer you'd like to install to, run the $PROGRAM_NAME application, and follow the on-screen prompts to complete installation.
Fedora Media Writer supports the following platforms:
Linux
Windows
Mac OS X

We have auto-detected that you are running Mac OS X and have offered that version for download below. If we have detected your operating system incorrectly or would like to download a different version, please click the "View all platform downloads" button below.
Fedora Media Writer will create a complete, running Fedora Workstation you can run right
away off of a USB drive. You can use the Live image to test and play with Fedora without making changes to your hard disk.
When you are ready, you can install Fedora to your hard disk from within this "live" version of Fedora Workstation.
